The National Pawnbrokers Association (NPA) is a USA-based trade association headquartered in Keller, Texas. The NPA was founded in 1987 to help the growing number of pawnbrokers in the United States. Today, there are more than 3000 members in the National Pawnbrokers Association.
As a trade association, the NPA is the pawning industry's only national association, offering guidance and support to pawnbrokers on how to be involved on a local, statewide and national basis.
